<th colspan="2" style="font-size:90%"><a href="/wiki/File:Gloriole.svg" class="image" title="Gloriole.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/Gloriole.svg/15px-Gloriole.svg.png" width="15" height="25" border="0" /></a> <b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Saints" title="Portal:Saints">Saints Portal</a></b></th>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The <b>Fourteen Holy Helpers</b> are a group of <a href="/wiki/Saint" title="Saint">saints</a> <a href="/wiki/Veneration" title="Veneration">venerated</a> together in <a href="/wiki/Roman_Catholicism" title="Roman Catholicism" class="mw-redirect">Roman Catholicism</a> because their <a href="/wiki/Intercession" title="Intercession">intercession</a> was thought to be particularly effective, especially against various <a href="/wiki/Disease" title="Disease">diseases</a>. This group of <i>Nothelfer</i> ("helpers in need") originated in the 14th century at first in the <a href="/wiki/Rhineland" title="Rhineland">Rhineland</a>, largely as a result of the <a href="/wiki/Epidemic" title="Epidemic">epidemic</a> (probably of <a href="/wiki/Bubonic_plague" title="Bubonic plague">bubonic plague</a>) that became known as the <a href="/wiki/Black_Death" title="Black Death">Black Death</a>.</p>
