<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Fourteen_Holy_Helpers&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">See also</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Franciscan_Monastery_in_Kada%C5%88" title="Franciscan Monastery in Kadaň">Franciscan Monastery in Kadaň</a> - a Franciscan monastery in the <a href="/wiki/Czech_Republic" title="Czech Republic">Czech Republic</a> with a church dedicated to the Holy Helpers.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Langheim_Abbey" title="Langheim Abbey">Langheim Abbey</a> - an abbey in <a href="/wiki/Lichtenfels,_Bavaria" title="Lichtenfels, Bavaria">Lichtenfels, Bavaria</a> where <a href="/wiki/Matthias_Gr%C3%BCnewald" title="Matthias Grünewald">Matthias Grünewald</a> painted his "Holy Helpers" altarpiece.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Four_Holy_Marshals" title="Four Holy Marshals">Four Holy Marshals</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Patron_saints_of_ailments,_illness_and_dangers" title="Patron saints of ailments, illness and dangers">Patron saints of ailments, illness and dangers</a> - the category of Roman Catholic saints to which the Holy Helpers belong.</li>
</ul>
